---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | GabrielsMind" description="About Gabriel and the GabrielsMind project.">
  <section class="about-hero section">
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1 class="section-title">Curiosity is what brought me into security. Building is what keeps me here.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
What keeps me engaged in cybersecurity is the need to understand. I want to know how systems are built, where trust breaks down, how behavior can be observed, and how defensive decisions actually hold up in practice.

For me, this is more than learning tools. It is a long-term way of thinking and working. That is why I build labs, document projects, and try to turn technical curiosity into practical security work.
        </p>

        <div class="card">
          <p>
            My background combines operations, leadership, and technical work. Because of that, I care less about sounding impressive and more about building things that are useful, explainable, and operationally real.
          </p>
          <p>
            This site is where I document that process clearly: what I build, how I think, and why certain technical decisions matter.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="about-image card image-shell">
        <img src="/images/about-reflection.jpg" alt="Gabriel working with a laptop in an urban setting" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .about-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 0.95fr;
      gap: 2rem;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .image-shell {
      padding: 0;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .image-shell img {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      min-height: 620px;
      object-fit: cover;
      display: block;
    }

    @media (max-width: 980px) {
      .about-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      .image-shell img {
        min-height: 420px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
